detail.title: Jinchao as Shentu Growth Manager
detail.description:
This proposal is to employ Jinchao as a Shentu Growth Manager. 

Jinchao's 5+ years in digital marketing, performance marketing, and PR equip her to elevate Shentu's digital presence and community engagement. 

Her role will focus on: 

- Enhancing Visibility : Enhancing Shentu's digital presence and performance marketing. 

- Communication strategies : Building effective communication strategies to grow the Shentu community. 

Jinchao will be a part-time resource, dedicating an average of 20-30 hours a week on average performing in her Shentu Growth Manager role. with compensation in Shentu from the "Shentu Community" Validator node. 

The Yes vote will be used as a signature of the Shentu Validators/Stakeholders and this will serve as a Contract between the Shentu Chain and Jinchao.

detail.title: Shentu Chain Loyalty Gratitude Distribution Proposal
detail.description:
This proposal aims to recognize and reward the valuable contributions of the Shentu Chain community and its loyal users. Their unwavering support has been instrumental in the growth and success of our blockchain platform. In line with our commitment to fostering a thriving ecosystem, we propose the implementation of the Shentu Loyalty Gratitude Distribution program.

 Shentu Loyalty Gratitude Distribution program:
 1. **Reward Amount**:
   We propose allocating an average of 10 CTK to each eligible address within the Shentu Chain network.
 2. **Eligibility Criteria**:
   Eligible addresses will be determined based on consistent engagement and active participation within the Shentu Chain ecosystem. This includes validators, delegators, developers, and community contributors who have demonstrated a commitment to the platform. The specific criteria for eligibility will be outlined in the official documentation.
 3. **Distribution Process**:
   The rewards will be distributed through DeepWallet, a trusted and secure platform of Shentu Chain. Detailed instructions and guidelines for claiming the rewards will be provided in the official [documentation](https://github.com/shentufoundation/mainnet/blob/main/shentu-2.2/distribution/README.md).

detail.title: Update Osmosis IBC Client on Shentu
detail.description:
This proposal will update the expired client on channel-8 between the Osmosis-1 and Shentu-2.2. Client 07-tendermint-9 has been expired due to the recent Shentu chain upgrade.

- By voting **YES**, the Shentu stakers, voice their support to unfreeze IBC channel-8 between shentu-2.2 and osmosis-1.

- By voting NO, the Shentu stakers voice their dissent to unfreeze IBC channel-8 between shentu-2.2 and osmosis-1.

**Details:**

In the case that this proposal goes through, client 07-tendermint-9 state will be substituted by the state of client 07-tendermint-25, what will unfreeze channel-8 and will allow users to transfer tokens between Osmosis and Shentu again.

detail.title: v1.3.0 Upgrade Proposal
detail.description:
This proposal is to vote for an upgrade to v1.3.0, which will be branched off and released from master branch commit c4902de745fae67a40aaf3047ad1304334975121.
Once the proposal passes the upgrade will take effect at height 1423600 or approximately on Feb 1st 4PM EST (9PM UTC).

link: https://github.com/certikfoundation/shentu/commit/c4902de745fae67a40aaf3047ad1304334975121

Upgrade instructions:
	1. Download or build the latest binaries
	2. Halt certikd process before the upgrade height(=1423600).
	3. Replace the binaries with the latest v1.3.0 binaries
	4. start certikd process with the new certikd binary.

NOTE: You do NOT have to run 'certikd unsafe-reset-all' for this upgrade. Running 'certikd unsafe-reset-all' will reset the chain's data, and you will have to re-sync from height 0.

The version includes a bugfix for shield service fee distribution with some minor API improvements and tests.

link: https://github.com/certikfoundation/shentu/commit/c4902de745fae67a40aaf3047ad1304334975121

Upgrade instructions:
	1. Download or build the latest binaries
	2. Halt certikd process before the upgrade height(=1423600).
	3. Replace the binaries with the latest v1.3.0 binaries
	4. start certikd process with the new certikd binary.

NOTE: You do NOT have to run 'certikd unsafe-reset-all' for this upgrade. Running 'certikd unsafe-reset-all' will reset the chain's data, and you will have to re-sync from height 0.

The version includes a bugfix for shield service fee distribution with some minor API improvements and tests.
